==Multi-combat mechanics==
[[File:Ancient Guthixian Temple multicombat areas.png|thumb|left|180px|Each multiway region of the temple.]]
Although the entire [[Ancient Guthixian Temple]] is considered a [[single-way combat]] zone by the game, the temple is a unique outlier in the fact that some areas are pseudo-[[multicombat area]]s. While in the temple, an icon that depicts a tormented demon's head can be seen in the user interface, indicating the amount of demons the player can attack at a time: either one, two, or three.

<gallery widths="25" heights="25">
Tormented demons multicombat I.png
Tormented demons multicombat II.png
Tormented demons multicombat III.png
</gallery>

* The north-western section of the dungeon (each containing a single demon) and the inner chamber where the Stone of Jas was once held is a proper single-way combat zone.
* The east and north-eastern sections of the dungeon is a doubles zone.
* The south-western section of the dungeon is a triples zone.

Tormented demons are unaggressive and will not attack unless attacked first.

==Fight overview==
{{main|Tormented Demon/Strategies}}

Tormented demons can pray against and attack using every [[combat style]]. They possess smart pathing, allowing them to move around objects, and can also stack on top of each other. If they cannot reach the player when attempting to melee, they will instead randomly fire magic and ranged attacks.

Every 150 health lost since their last prayer swap (roughly 25% of their max health), they will change their protection prayer to the last combat style they were damaged with, and will stop attacking for 6 [[tick]]s (3.6s).

They will briefly bind the player in place roughly every 60 ticks (36s) and disable run ({{Key press|Ctrl}} clicking still allows running), then release two fire bombs: one on the player's position as of the start of the attack, and a second on a random one of the 8 adjacent squares, assuming that it is a walkable tile. The bind will then be released and players have 2 ticks to move off of the target tiles before they explode. Demons always change their combat style after this attack.

Tormented demons usually have a fire shield that reduces damage done by non-[[demonbane weapons]]/[[demonbane spells|spells]] and non-[[abyssal weapons]] by 20%. They will drop this shield after their first attack and after each fire bomb attack; the shield remains down until they are attacked once. Slower weapons will deal significant bonus damage to unshielded tormented demons. They also become defenseless from approximately 30 ticks (18s) into the fight until after their fire bomb attack, after which the 30 tick timer begins again. Attacking them while defenseless will provide 100% accuracy meaning guaranteed hits.

If the player chooses to attack multiple tormented demons simultaneously, their attack behaviour changes: one will use melee if possible, and the other magic or ranged, and their attacks start out staggered so they can be prayed against. If three or more demons are attacking the player, the third and any more demons will release single bombs at the player.

If demons are forced out of combat due to teleportation or being unable to attack their target, they will restore their health to full.

