==Historical==
Tormented demons were released alongside While Guthix Sleeps on [[26 November]] [[2008]]. They are nearly the same as their ''RuneScape'' counterparts but with several differences:

*There are significantly more tormented demons throughout the entirety of the Ancient Guthixian Temple. In ''RuneScape'', there are only six demons, all of whom are near the plinth where the Stone of Jas once was, while in ''Old School RuneScape'', there are twenty-six; eight by the plinth, two by the door leading to the inner section of the temple, eight to the western section of the temple (one each to the north-western chambers, and two sets of three to the southwest) and another eight to the eastern dolmens, in four sets of two.
*The tormented demons in ''Old School RuneScape'' are unaggressive, whereas those in ''RuneScape'' never become tolerant to the player.
*In ''Old School RuneScape'', tormented demons are considered [[greater demon]]s for the purpose of a slayer assignment. In ''RuneScape'', tormented demons were not an assignable Slayer task for a considerable amount of time after release. Later on, they were allowed to be assigned as part of a Slayer task, though the player had to pay 50 slayer points to be assigned them; they could also be killed as part of a {{RSL|demons (Slayer assignment)|demon cluster task}} on [[8 July]] [[2019]].
*While the demons in both games attack with multiple combat styles, their special attacks are quite different:
**The demons in ''RuneScape'' would periodically throw an AoE magic attack when changing combat styles. In ''Old School RuneScape'', they instead bind the player before launching magical fire around them, dealing heavy damage if not avoided.
**If the demon was using melee but was attacked from a distance, in ''RuneScape'' it would change combat styles immediately. In ''Old School RuneScape'', they will only do so if they cannot reach their target, but would quickly revert to melee once they returned in range.
*The demons in ''RuneScape'' would change overhead prayers after taking a minimum of 30 (3,000) damage, while the demons in ''Old School RuneScape'' do so after taking a minimum of 150 damage.
*The demons' shield effects were much stronger in ''RuneScape'', it would reduce damage by 75% of the original amount, necessitating {{RSL|darklight}} or {{RSL|holy water}} to remove it. In ''Old School RuneScape'', the shield only reduces non-demonic damage by 20%.
*The demons in ''Old School RuneScape'' take additional damage from 5/6/7-tick weapons at specific intervals (which likewise attack faster at these intervals), whereas this mechanic is not featured in ''RuneScape''.
*The demons in ''RuneScape'' originally had four unique drops on release: in addition to the {{RSL|dragon claws}}, they also dropped the {{RSL|ruined dragon armour slice}}, {{RSL|ruined dragon armour lump}} and {{RSL|ruined dragon armour shard}}, which would be used to create the {{RSL|dragon platebody}}. A fifth drop, {{RSL|dragon limbs}}, was added on [[20 November]] [[2012]]. As these rewards were already present in ''Old School RuneScape'' (the [[dragon claws]] from the [[Chambers of Xeric]], the [[dragon platebody]] from [[Dragon Slayer II]] with a [[dragon metal shard]] and [[dragon metal lump]], and the [[dragon limbs]] from [[Adamant dragon|adamant]] and [[Rune dragon|rune dragons]]), the demons were instead given different rewards, namely the [[tormented synapse]] and [[burning claw]], as their unique drops.
*Tormented demons in ''RuneScape'' were originally released with 326 hitpoints and zero offensive or defensive stats. The demons in ''Old School RuneScape'' have 600 hitpoints and have offensive and defensive stats added to give them a distinct weakness:{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://x.com/JagexAsh/status/1749777281675907450|date=23 January 2024|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/3svFq|archivedate=11 July 2024|quote=[I was wondering what stats they had before then. Is it possible to find out please?] Attack 255
Strength 166
Defence 300
Magic 255
Ranged 255
Lifepoints 3260 (presumably that's 326 HP)
No defensive bonuses.|name=Tormented demon 2008 stats}}
